						               													<description>The Atrum is what comes after death, a dark and desolate place. Any creature or being that dies on the material plane ends up in the Atrum. The bodies are transferred from one plane to another through the earth, being buried in the middle of both places. The only exception is the Crawlers, who roam the Atrum engaging in fierce battles where they unleash their full power.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Atrum Arena is a large format Premium Trading Card Game (TCG) created by Estudio Fedorian, where each participant makes a team of three lords and/or ladies of darkness, known as &amp;ldquo;Crawlers&amp;rdquo;. These Crawlers are represented in the game in the form of spectacular holographic premium cards. With them you will face the teams of your opponents, trying to defeat all of your opponets Crawlers, one by one and lead your team to victory. All of this using the combined powers of your Crawlers, the synergy between them and the faithful Minions, which will be drawn from a common deck as a consumable resourse to make the Crawler's powers.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Atrum Arena is a true new game concept, not only because of its mechanics that mix resource management, hand management and a bit of luck forcing, but also because it brings to the tables its exclusive &amp;ldquo;build and choice of actions menu&amp;rdquo;.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At the same time it is about luxury collecting, but extremely friendly and accessible, being the game of this type that can be started faster and more easily.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
